
Collection
- Collection is hold same type of data or different type of data.

Array
- Array is collection of same type of data or different type of data. It has fixed size
  - IntArray : That hold int data
  - BooleanArray: Hold boolean data
  - DoubleArray: Hold double data
  - ByteArray: Hold byte data
  - LongArray: Hold long data
  - ShortArray: Hold short data
  - FloatArray: Hold float data
- function
  - arrayOf<String> : holding string data type
  - arrayOf<Fruit> : holding object or model class data
  - array(1,2,"Raj",20.5) : holding different type of data



Immutable collection
Means you only read the value but you cannot write to it.

- List : listOf -> List is similar to arrayOf but it has more helper methods
- Set : setOf -> Store unique values in group
- map : mapOf -> Store key value paired data

Mutable collection
Means you can read or write data to it.

- Mutable List : ArrayList, arrayListOf, mutableListOf
- Mutable Set : mutableSetOf, hashSetOf
- Mutable Map : HashMap, hashMapOf, mutableMapOf
